args: A duskhawk... The guild must have sent\nanother message.
Is someone after the life of\n{player_name} again?
Good boy. Let me see the letter.
＂The game is up, my dear Reaper.\nThe guild knows that you have betrayed us.＂
＂Your betrayal will cost a lonely girl her life.\nBut should you wish for her to be spared...＂
＂Should you wish for her to be spared,\noffer me the life of the seventh heir to the\nthrone, Prince {player_name}.＂
This sounds like just the kind of thing the\nguild would do.
Your luck ran out when you involved\nyourself with the Reaper.
Oh, you've never heard that name? Ha!\nWhat a wretched excuse for a man.
It looks like I've been giving him too much\ncredit—I never knew he was too cowardly\nto properly say good-bye to his past.
I wish I could deny that.
The tearful reunion can wait until later.\nI hope you brought what I asked for!
I asked you for his life, Reaper!\nYet this man still lives!

In this trade, who deals the fatal blow
matters. I thought it would be better to
bring him to you this way and let you
claim the kill.
He's bound tightly. Killing him now would\nbe a simple matter.
Heh. How very considerate of you.\nStill, you're not wrong.
We're trading him for her; we'll walk them\nforward at the same time. Agreed?
They're wasting no time in getting to their\ntouching reunion. Gya, it makes me sick.
All right. Let's get this over with, shall we,\nYour Highness?
Ha ha ha! If you want to blame anyone,\nblame yourself for being naive enough\nto take in the Reaper.
Gaaah! Wh-what just happened?!\nYou were tied up!
Looks like I'm not the naive one.
Hawk is our friend now—your underhanded\ntrickery won't work on him!
He deliberately didn't bind you properly?!\nCurse him!
But you're in our territory now, so don't\nthink you're going home in one piece!
Take them out, my elite guild assassins!\nI will pay triple the usual fee!
Sorry, but there ain't many of them\n＂elite assassins＂ left.
Course I did. {player_name}'s\none of us—and so are you!
I can't believe you were all willing to help\na man like me.
Of course we were. Whatever you might\nhave done in the past, I still believe that\nyour feelings right now are genuine.
And that you truly want to live in a\nbetter world!
This damn farce has gone on long enough!
Don't move! If you so much as twitch,\nyou're going to have a hole in your head.
You should know what the Reaper is\ncapable of better than anyone.
Now go home, Villea. Forget about me.
But I want you to come with me, Silva!
...I cannot. The man you knew is dead.
No! He's right here in front of me!
Silva was a man who dreamed of the\nhappiness of one woman, and one woman\nonly—you.
He was willing to sacrifice anything,\nor anyone, for that.
But that is not true for the man in front of\nyou. He is simply a hawk.
Indeed. A hawk who dreams of a world\nwithout victims.
